The paper deals with the fundamental idea of shortest augmenting paths in maximum matching and maximum flow algorithms, which is a topic in both data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem being studied is an online bipartite matching problem on trees, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the total length of augmenting paths, which could be considered an information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) problem.
